Write a Java program to implement a simple calculator.

## Assistant:
Here is a Java program to implement a simple calculator:

```Java
import java.util.*;

public class SimpleCalculator {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        double n1, n2;
        String operation;

        System.out.println("Enter first number: ");
        n1 = sc.nextDouble();
        System.out.println("Enter second number: ");
        n2 = sc.nextDouble();
        System.out.println("Enter an operation (+,-,*,/): ");
        operation = sc.next();

        switch (operation)  {
            case "+":
                System.out.println("The result is: " + (n1 + n2));
                break;

            case "-":
                System.out.println("The result is: " + (n1 - n2));
                break;

            case "*":
                System.out.println("The result is: " + (n1 * n2));
                break;

            case "/":
                System.out.println("The result is: " + (n1 / n2));
                break;

            default:
                System.out.println("Invalid operation!");
                break;
        }
    }
}
```
This program prompts the user to enter two numbers and an arithmetic operation, then performs the specified operation on the numbers and outputs the result.

